runs.comm: just a hint of swing and he opens the face and dabs it towards backward point
nice line and length, he goes right back and defends
angles towards the pads and he shuffles and clips it to fine leg
stays back and clips it softly past square leg, he importantly kept it along the ground, he was out caught in that position yesterday
stays back and taps it down to backward point
bangs it in short and he ducks under the bouncer
nice delivery, dead straight forces him on the backfoot to defend
nice and straight again, lands it on the seam, he stays on the backfoot and defends
hits the deck hard and its the slower bouncer, just sails over the helmet, Ojha tries to hook
cramps him up for room and he taps it back to the bowler
short and a touch wide and he fails to put that away past backward point
chops it towards point and tries to pinch a single, Vijay sends him back
now he bowls it fuller and tempts him to come forward for the drive, the away movement beats him, lovely delivery and good over
appeal for lbw! Full and hits his pads outside the line of leg, Vijay ought to have put that away
that's the Vijay we know! Picks a good length ball, swivels and pulls over square leg, uses the crease well and completes the shot, well played
lovely shot! Mpofu bowls the slower ball and Vijay stays at the crease and swings across the line over wide long-on, lot of elevation on that shot
bangs it in short and he ducks under the bouncer
taps it towards long-on
short and wide and he spanks that, he rolls his wrists and bisects the gap between point and cover point
stays back and punches it towards mid-on
Chatara slides down the leg side, Vijay tries to glance it away
tempts him to go for the massive lofted on drive, he swishes at thin air
hits his pads and rolls away down to short midwicket
tucks it just wide of mid-on and sets off for a single
cramps him up for room and he steers it down to cover point
in the slot for Vijay and he capitalises, overpitched on the off stump, he uses the crease, gets under the bounce and launches him straight over the bowler's head
slightly short down the leg side and wide called
comes down the track and tries to biff that but the bowler holds the length back, Vijay misses it completely, Taibu aims for the stumps and Vijay was back just in time
punches it with a straight bat down to mid-off
tucks it down to short fine leg
down the track and he pushes it towards mid-on
makes room and dabs it towards short third man
he makes room and comes down the pitch a few paces and effortlessly lofts over mid-off
looked like a good shot but straight to the fielder, he gets on his knee and plays a well-timed slog sweep but Chatara's there at deep square leg to take it
turns it wide of midwicket and takes a single
opens the face of the bat and dabs it down to point
chases a wide delivery outside off, feet rooted to the crease
full marks for placement! The ball was angled wide across the left hander and Raina despite being rooted to the crease managed to punch that in the air past cover and extra cover
too wide outside off and even Raina couldn't chase that
full outside off and steered wide of backward point
turns it with soft hands towards midwicket and jogs the single
chips down the track and lofts over midwicket
turns it towards short fine leg and turns down the single
turns it to the on side again
Vintage Vijay! He comes down the track a few paces and lofts crisply through the line over wide long-on, crisply hit
pushes it to the off side
tossed up on leg and clipped to the on side
sweeps hard but finds short fine leg
turns it with soft hands towards short square leg
bowls it flatter and he pulls him down to deep square leg
Vijay makes room and Price follows him, sprays it wide down the leg side, the keeper fumbles and they take a run as well
waits for the ball to come on to him and clips him down to midwicket
gets forward and drives down the ground to long-off
comes down the pitch and tucks it in the air over midwicket
taps it towards cover and he turns down the single
stays back and punches it towards long-off
drops it short, he stays back and clips it wide of square leg
drops it towards cover and sets off, a misfield on the dive allows a second run
makes a bit of room and squeezes it past the gap at point
tossed up down the legside and he tries to sweep, under edge beats short fine leg
drops it short, he swivels, goes right back and clubs it over midwicket
turns it wide of short fine leg for a single
opens the face and dabs it down to backward point
stays back and pulls and just wide of Price at deep square leg, reaches him on the first bounce
slog sweep but one bounce to deep midwicket
pushes it back to the bowler
keeps low and nearly bowls him through the gate
stays back and tucks him down to deep square leg
pushes it back to the bowler
his favourite on side area, he comes down the pitch and lofts effortlessly over midwicket, good follow through
pushes a low full toss back to the bowler
pushes it towards mid-off and Raina thinks of a single, sends Vijay back and the throw was wide
tucks it to the on side behind square
stays back and punches in the air down to long-off
punches it just wide of cover
he drops it a fraction short, Raina stays at the crease and has a free swing of the arms and clubs it over deep midwicket
turns it to deep square leg and he pushes for the second, the throw wasn't good enough
opens the face and dabs it down to third man
full on the pads and clipped away down to deep midwicket
turns it towards midwicket and Lamb has a shy at the stumps, misses it
tries to dig out a yorker outside off and he ends up getting an inside edge to the on side
low full toss and he clubs it across the line but it goes one bounce to Mpofu at deep midwicket
full outside off and squeezed out to backward point
full on middle and leg and driven down to long-on
he stays at the crease and slogs past midwicket, beats a diving Coventry at deep midwicket
very risky! He makes a lot of room and at the last minute he dabs it to third man, had he missed he would have been history
comes down a few paces and scoops him over square leg, good improvisation
punched down the ground to long-off
gets an outside edge past the keeper down to third man
full outside off and driven down to deep cover
turns it to the on side for a single
plays an ungainly slog down to deep midwicket
the slower ball consumes him, he comes down the track attempting to loft over long-on but the lack of pace forces him to check his shot, Lamb runs forward and takes the catch
full outside off and driven down to long-off
punches it towards cover and thinks of a single, sent back, the throw is wide

effortless! It was a friendly full toss and Raina moved across slightly and lofted it crisply over long-off, seemed like it would head down the fielder's throat but the timing was exquisite, that's his fifty too
on the blockhole and dug out back to the bowler
full outside off and he squeezes it out to deep cover
on the pads and he easily clips it down to long leg, the fielder runs across to cut it off
tries to pull but the ball hits his gloves and rolls towards the keeper
short again and he controls the pull to fine leg
punched down the ground to long-on, thinks of a second
gets on his knee and scoops it over extra cover, the fielder cuts it off
full and wide outside off and he gets on his his knee and scoops it over extra cover and finds the gap
full outside off and he fails to squeeze out the yorker
punched on the up down to long-off, the fielder does well to cut it off
scoops a low full toss over cover, one bounce
really wide outside off and he reaches out and squeezes it away down to third man
good yorker on  the pads and the ball rolls to the on side
the slowest of slow bouncers, landed somewhere mid pitch, Rains wasnt sure what to do with it and then decided to upper cut it and misses it, too wide outside off
full and wide outside off
plays a short arm pull down to deep midwicket
tries to seal it with a big hit, gets a thick top edge and he knows he's a goner, Masakadza takes it in front of mid-on
tries to smash that down the leg side but wide called
punched crisply straight to cover, the throw is wide but they don't take the overthrow
pitched up and he biffs it down the ground wide of the bowler and mid-on
